The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Indian shot in US store
                                                                                                               Indian shot in US store
                            
	Washington, June 19 (PTI): A 26-year-old Indian-origin youth working at a convenience store in the US was shot dead by robbers, but shoppers made no attempt to help him or call police.        
	Gurjeet Singh of Gary, Indiana, worked as a clerk in a store attached to his uncles gas station. He was killed on June 14.         
	The police have released video footage captured by surveillance cameras showing four men entering the Gary mini mart and gas station. One is seen rushing towards Gurjeet. Although the shooting was not captured, the footage shows shoppers walking past as Gurjeet lay dying.        
	Any time you see a crime and dont report it, thats bad enough, but when you see a violent act... and dont call attention to it, that says something about your soul, a detective was quoted as saying.                                                                                                                                                                            
